<inglise> (3) the result of applying these standards should be to remove products of unsatisfactory quality from the market, to bring production into line with consumer requirements, to facilitate trade relationships based on fair competition, and thereby to help make production more profitable: </inglise>
<eesti> 3) nende standardite kohaldamine peaks ebarahuldava kvaliteediga tooted turult k&otilde;rvaldama, viima tootmise vastavusse tarbijate n&otilde;udmistega ja h&otilde;lbustama ausal konkurentsil p&otilde;hinevaid kaubandussuhteid, parandades seel&auml;bi tootmise tasuvust; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) the standards are applicable at all stages of marketing. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) neid standardeid kohaldatakse k&otilde;ikidel turustusetappidel. </eesti>
<inglise> Carriage over a great distance, storage for a certain length of time and the various handling operations which the products undergo may bring about deterioration due to the biological development of the products or their perishability. </inglise>
